1
00:01:31,100 --> 00:01:34,980
=Wonder Wall=

2
00:01:35,020 --> 00:01:37,910
=Episode 10=

3
00:01:38,400 --> 00:01:38,760
San.

4
00:01:38,920 --> 00:01:39,760
San. Calm down!

5
00:01:39,920 --> 00:01:40,680
San! San!

6
00:01:40,760 --> 00:01:41,480
Don't scare me like that.

7
00:01:41,480 --> 00:01:42,159
Jesus, what can I do?

8
00:01:42,359 --> 00:01:42,719
San.

9
00:01:43,000 --> 00:01:44,079
Calm down!

10
00:01:44,200 --> 00:01:44,519
San!

11
00:01:44,719 --> 00:01:45,159
San!

12
00:01:45,480 --> 00:01:45,920
Bro.

13
00:01:46,040 --> 00:01:46,799
You're finally back!

14
00:01:46,799 --> 00:01:47,680
He was out of control.

15
00:01:47,719 --> 00:01:48,680
Stop babbling. Grab a towel.

16
00:01:48,879 --> 00:01:50,200
San has had epilepsy since he was a kid.

17
00:01:51,359 --> 00:01:52,000
What's this?

18
00:01:52,239 --> 00:01:53,079
Alcohol. Rubbing it on him.

19
00:01:53,120 --> 00:01:53,760
Where do I apply it?

20
00:01:53,760 --> 00:01:54,319
Chin!

21
00:01:54,719 --> 00:01:55,319
Chin.

22
00:01:55,680 --> 00:01:56,560
Right, that's it.

23
00:01:56,599 --> 00:01:57,239
Anywhere else?

24
00:01:57,280 --> 00:01:57,760
Armpits!

25
00:01:57,799 --> 00:01:58,200
Armpits.

26
00:01:58,280 --> 00:01:58,640
Yes.

27
00:01:58,640 --> 00:01:58,879
Armpits.

28
00:01:59,280 --> 00:02:00,159
Legs!

29
00:02:00,359 --> 00:02:01,079
Thighs or calves?

30
00:02:01,079 --> 00:02:01,680
Thighs!

31
00:02:04,280 --> 00:02:06,519
- San!
- San!

32
00:02:07,760 --> 00:02:08,159
San!

33
00:02:08,479 --> 00:02:08,879
San!

34
00:02:09,039 --> 00:02:09,759
Hold still, San!

35
00:02:11,319 --> 00:02:11,680
Bro.

36
00:02:12,680 --> 00:02:14,000
Should we take him to the hospital?

37
00:02:16,520 --> 00:02:17,120
Hospital?

38
00:02:18,319 --> 00:02:19,000
You have money?

39
00:02:25,199 --> 00:02:25,800
But...

40
00:02:26,400 --> 00:02:27,840
What if he dies right here?

41
00:02:29,680 --> 00:02:30,719
He just has a fever.

42
00:02:30,719 --> 00:02:31,599
He's not going to die.

43
00:02:35,039 --> 00:02:35,439
Wait.

44
00:02:36,680 --> 00:02:37,319
Could he have

45
00:02:37,319 --> 00:02:38,479
angered something underground

46
00:02:39,080 --> 00:02:40,000
while digging that tunnel?

47
00:02:40,080 --> 00:02:41,520
Maybe I should burn some incense.

48
00:02:41,560 --> 00:02:42,719
He was just stunned.

49
00:02:42,759 --> 00:02:44,039
It has nothing to do with that.

50
00:02:44,199 --> 00:02:45,719
Who's ever seen that much money?

51
00:02:45,759 --> 00:02:46,840
Anyone would be stunned.

52
00:02:49,400 --> 00:02:49,639
But...

53
00:02:49,719 --> 00:02:50,639
I think

54
00:02:50,680 --> 00:02:51,439
those two aren't good people.

55
00:02:51,599 --> 00:02:52,560
What if they call the cops?

56
00:02:53,120 --> 00:02:54,360
San can't run away now.

57
00:02:54,520 --> 00:02:55,719
You fool!

58
00:02:55,759 --> 00:02:56,280
If they call them,

59
00:02:56,280 --> 00:02:57,360
who's getting caught?

60
00:02:58,599 --> 00:02:59,039
Stupid.

61
00:03:00,479 --> 00:03:01,280
Right.

62
00:03:03,319 --> 00:03:03,840
No need to escape.

63
00:03:04,840 --> 00:03:05,840
Go after those two idiots.

64
00:03:08,599 --> 00:03:08,960
Ghost.

65
00:03:09,560 --> 00:03:10,000
Ghost.

66
00:03:18,599 --> 00:03:19,680
I've been on edge all day.

67
00:03:21,240 --> 00:03:22,280
I feel trapped in this room.

68
00:03:22,280 --> 00:03:23,039
But if I'm going out,

69
00:03:23,039 --> 00:03:23,840
I feel suffocated too.

70
00:03:25,800 --> 00:03:27,360
I used to love this basement.

71
00:03:27,560 --> 00:03:28,479
Very much.

72
00:03:29,000 --> 00:03:29,800
Everything here

73
00:03:30,599 --> 00:03:32,240
felt golden.

74
00:03:32,919 --> 00:03:34,319
The money was meant to serve us.

75
00:03:34,360 --> 00:03:35,240
But now?

76
00:03:35,240 --> 00:03:35,960
We became the servants instead.

77
00:03:36,240 --> 00:03:37,080
We panicked

78
00:03:37,240 --> 00:03:38,199
because

79
00:03:38,479 --> 00:03:39,919
there were too many names,

80
00:03:40,120 --> 00:03:41,039
too many leads.

81
00:03:41,120 --> 00:03:42,120
We couldn't make sense of it.

82
00:03:42,439 --> 00:03:43,280
So we panicked.

83
00:03:44,479 --> 00:03:44,960
But...

84
00:03:45,400 --> 00:03:45,879
Hey, guys.

85
00:03:47,800 --> 00:03:48,439
Are you here?

86
00:03:49,879 --> 00:03:50,360
Don't move!

87
00:03:50,439 --> 00:03:50,960
Stay put!

88
00:03:51,199 --> 00:03:52,599
Don't shoot. Don't shoot.

89
00:03:52,759 --> 00:03:53,879
We're not bad people.

90
00:03:53,879 --> 00:03:54,479
What do you want?

91
00:03:54,599 --> 00:03:55,719
Sorry, bro.

92
00:03:55,719 --> 00:03:56,960
We busted through your basement.

93
00:03:56,960 --> 00:03:58,159
Shut up! Step back!

94
00:03:58,199 --> 00:03:58,680
Move!

95
00:04:07,840 --> 00:04:09,120
Aren't there three of you?

96
00:04:09,199 --> 00:04:11,120
That guy's freaked out.

97
00:04:11,159 --> 00:04:12,319
He's lying down at home.

98
00:04:12,400 --> 00:04:14,280
Nearly scared to death.

99
00:04:14,599 --> 00:04:15,639
Let's cut to the chase.

100
00:04:15,759 --> 00:04:16,800
Why are you digging a tunnel?

101
00:04:17,600 --> 00:04:18,519
Why? We...

102
00:04:18,879 --> 00:04:19,759
Start from the beginning!

103
00:04:20,920 --> 00:04:21,639
Well...

104
00:04:21,759 --> 00:04:22,519
Because...

105
00:04:23,600 --> 00:04:24,399
Let me do the talking.

106
00:04:24,959 --> 00:04:26,399
When I was born,

107
00:04:26,480 --> 00:04:27,399
it was pouring rain.

108
00:04:27,480 --> 00:04:29,199
So my great-grandmother

109
00:04:29,360 --> 00:04:31,240
put the character "rain" in my name.

110
00:04:31,439 --> 00:04:32,800
Then when I grew up,

111
00:04:32,920 --> 00:04:33,480
I wondered...

112
00:04:33,480 --> 00:04:34,639
Stop, stop!

113
00:04:34,720 --> 00:04:36,000
Why did you guys dig tunnels?

114
00:04:36,040 --> 00:04:36,399
Right.

115
00:04:36,560 --> 00:04:36,879
Hurry up!

116
00:04:36,879 --> 00:04:38,519
Well... Hold on...

117
00:04:38,879 --> 00:04:40,639
Tomb raider. San.

118
00:04:42,199 --> 00:04:43,439
Tomb raider.

119
00:04:43,959 --> 00:04:44,279
San.

120
00:04:44,439 --> 00:04:45,439
He said

121
00:04:45,439 --> 00:04:46,600
he comes from a line of tomb raiders.

122
00:04:46,600 --> 00:04:47,680
Born to dig, trained to dig.

123
00:04:47,759 --> 00:04:49,199
Of course, we didn't believe him.

124
00:04:49,240 --> 00:04:50,680
He looked like some scruffy weasel,

125
00:04:50,680 --> 00:04:51,720
always carrying a turtle shell,

126
00:04:51,720 --> 00:04:52,800
wandering here and there,

127
00:04:52,800 --> 00:04:54,000
digging this way and that.

128
00:04:54,120 --> 00:04:54,600
Right?

129
00:04:55,160 --> 00:04:55,680
Yes. Right.

130
00:04:55,759 --> 00:04:57,680
Then he just dug his way through.

131
00:04:57,879 --> 00:04:59,680
Why were you digging this tunnel?

132
00:04:59,839 --> 00:05:00,319
For money.

133
00:05:01,399 --> 00:05:01,920
What money?

134
00:05:02,120 --> 00:05:03,439
How did you know there was money here?

135
00:05:03,720 --> 00:05:07,040
I didn't know about down here.

136
00:05:07,560 --> 00:05:08,839
But that wall upstairs...

137
00:05:09,160 --> 00:05:10,040
I built it.

138
00:05:10,760 --> 00:05:14,560
(2012)

139
00:05:19,439 --> 00:05:20,560
Hurry. San.

140
00:05:31,759 --> 00:05:32,680
Do it properly.

141
00:05:33,360 --> 00:05:34,199
Be quick!

142
00:05:35,199 --> 00:05:35,759
What are you doing?

143
00:05:36,600 --> 00:05:37,519
Who is that on the second floor?

144
00:05:37,680 --> 00:05:38,399
Where is your helmet?

145
00:05:38,800 --> 00:05:39,360
I'm talking to you.

146
00:05:39,519 --> 00:05:39,959
Get down here.

147
00:05:40,240 --> 00:05:40,920
Come here.

148
00:05:41,560 --> 00:05:42,279
Put your helmet on.

149
00:05:45,240 --> 00:05:45,600
Don't you know

150
00:05:45,600 --> 00:05:46,600
there is an inspection coming?

151
00:05:47,160 --> 00:05:47,759
Sorry.

152
00:05:47,759 --> 00:05:49,240
He's new. It won't happen again.

153
00:05:49,759 --> 00:05:50,319
Your man?

154
00:05:50,480 --> 00:05:50,959
Yes, yes.

155
00:05:51,120 --> 00:05:52,199
Safety is no small matter.

156
00:05:52,199 --> 00:05:53,240
I keep saying this.

157
00:05:53,240 --> 00:05:53,720
Every single time!

158
00:05:53,959 --> 00:05:55,120
Standing there with no helmet?

159
00:05:55,279 --> 00:05:57,040
The inspection is tomorrow.

160
00:05:57,120 --> 00:05:58,800
Who takes the fall if this goes wrong?

161
00:06:00,240 --> 00:06:00,680
Put it on!

162
00:06:01,000 --> 00:06:01,959
One serious mistake,

163
00:06:02,040 --> 00:06:02,800
and nobody gets paid.

164
00:06:02,920 --> 00:06:03,720
What is the fine for no helmet?

165
00:06:05,439 --> 00:06:05,959
100 yuan.

166
00:06:06,399 --> 00:06:06,879
Make it 200.

167
00:06:07,079 --> 00:06:07,759
Teach him a lesson.

168
00:06:08,639 --> 00:06:09,480
That is 200 off your pay!

169
00:06:10,000 --> 00:06:11,240
No helmet, 200 off!

170
00:06:11,720 --> 00:06:13,160
You over there.

171
00:06:14,639 --> 00:06:15,279
What are you waiting for?

172
00:06:18,720 --> 00:06:20,360
Get moving, everyone!

173
00:06:21,040 --> 00:06:22,480
Find me two men for a side job.

174
00:06:23,279 --> 00:06:23,879
Sure. Sure.

175
00:06:24,199 --> 00:06:24,600
Okay.

176
00:06:24,600 --> 00:06:25,279
No small matters.

177
00:06:25,639 --> 00:06:25,959
Hey!

178
00:06:26,079 --> 00:06:26,839
You!

179
00:06:26,839 --> 00:06:27,879
Come here. Hurry.

180
00:06:29,639 --> 00:06:30,079
Listen.

181
00:06:30,439 --> 00:06:31,720
The boss has a finished villa

182
00:06:31,720 --> 00:06:32,120
over there.

183
00:06:32,160 --> 00:06:32,800
Find me

184
00:06:32,839 --> 00:06:33,920
a few quick-handed men

185
00:06:34,120 --> 00:06:34,920
for some work there.

186
00:06:34,920 --> 00:06:35,519
It is for the boss.

187
00:06:35,560 --> 00:06:36,000
Sure.

188
00:06:36,240 --> 00:06:36,959
No problem.

189
00:06:37,160 --> 00:06:38,079
Keep your helmet on.

190
00:06:38,240 --> 00:06:39,240
I'm good. I'm good.

191
00:06:42,199 --> 00:06:43,279
Build me this wall.

192
00:06:43,600 --> 00:06:44,040
Here.

193
00:06:44,160 --> 00:06:45,160
It will be the TV wall.

194
00:06:45,199 --> 00:06:46,920
From here all the way to here,

195
00:06:46,959 --> 00:06:48,279
make it hollow inside.

196
00:06:48,839 --> 00:06:49,959
Leave enough room.

197
00:06:50,120 --> 00:06:51,000
And this part here,

198
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:52,000
right in the middle,

199
00:06:52,040 --> 00:06:53,120
leave space

200
00:06:53,120 --> 00:06:53,639
for the TV mount.

201
00:06:53,720 --> 00:06:54,800
My TV's 75 inches.

202
00:06:54,879 --> 00:06:55,240
Okay.

203
00:06:55,240 --> 00:06:55,639
Sir,

204
00:06:55,800 --> 00:06:57,040
this is a fireplace.

205
00:06:57,079 --> 00:06:58,319
And if you build

206
00:06:58,439 --> 00:06:59,399
such a thick cavity wall,

207
00:06:59,399 --> 00:07:00,079
it will not look good.

208
00:07:00,199 --> 00:07:01,160
Who is designing this?

209
00:07:01,240 --> 00:07:02,000
Who is living here?

210
00:07:02,120 --> 00:07:02,759
You.

211
00:07:03,079 --> 00:07:03,560
You.

212
00:07:03,959 --> 00:07:04,639
Then stop talking.

213
00:07:04,680 --> 00:07:05,839
You have two days.

214
00:07:05,839 --> 00:07:06,680
Finish it in two.

215
00:07:06,680 --> 00:07:07,519
Two days?

216
00:07:07,600 --> 00:07:08,959
Far from enough.

217
00:07:09,120 --> 00:07:09,879
A wall this wide,

218
00:07:09,879 --> 00:07:10,680
how could we possibly...?

219
00:07:10,680 --> 00:07:11,879
Two days are fine.

220
00:07:12,319 --> 00:07:12,720
Sir.

221
00:07:13,000 --> 00:07:14,160
When will you settle

222
00:07:14,160 --> 00:07:15,240
our wages?

223
00:07:15,279 --> 00:07:16,199
As I said,

224
00:07:16,240 --> 00:07:17,360
once the main site

225
00:07:17,360 --> 00:07:17,959
is settled,

226
00:07:17,959 --> 00:07:18,879
I will pay you together.

227
00:07:18,879 --> 00:07:19,680
What's the rush?

228
00:07:19,759 --> 00:07:20,240
No way.

229
00:07:20,319 --> 00:07:21,720
The site is one job.

230
00:07:21,759 --> 00:07:22,639
This is private work.

231
00:07:22,680 --> 00:07:23,439
And this wall...

232
00:07:23,439 --> 00:07:24,319
Take it

233
00:07:24,360 --> 00:07:25,240
or leave it.

234
00:07:25,560 --> 00:07:26,279
With all these men here,

235
00:07:26,279 --> 00:07:27,160
I can replace you in a minute.

236
00:07:27,319 --> 00:07:28,160
We can do it.

237
00:07:28,160 --> 00:07:29,920
All right, fine.

238
00:07:34,360 --> 00:07:35,680
San. Go to pee.

239
00:07:41,360 --> 00:07:42,000
Got it.

240
00:07:55,959 --> 00:07:56,879
Always peeing.

241
00:08:47,759 --> 00:08:48,440
What did you see?

242
00:08:48,960 --> 00:08:50,399
Nothing. I saw nothing.

243
00:08:50,399 --> 00:08:51,080
I was just peeing.

244
00:08:51,279 --> 00:08:52,200
Whatever you saw,

245
00:08:52,240 --> 00:08:52,840
forget it.

246
00:08:52,879 --> 00:08:53,440
Understand?

247
00:08:56,240 --> 00:08:56,840
I know you.

248
00:08:57,000 --> 00:08:57,840
You built that wall.

249
00:08:58,679 --> 00:08:59,639
I know where you live.

250
00:08:59,720 --> 00:09:00,399
Want to stay alive?

251
00:09:01,279 --> 00:09:02,519
Then forget every last bit of it.

252
00:09:08,799 --> 00:09:09,679
Sir, no.

253
00:09:09,799 --> 00:09:10,799
Take it.

254
00:09:11,240 --> 00:09:12,320
Take the money and vanish.

255
00:09:12,639 --> 00:09:13,559
I don't want to see you again.

256
00:09:13,919 --> 00:09:14,440
Understand?

257
00:09:15,039 --> 00:09:15,480
Vanish.

258
00:09:15,480 --> 00:09:15,919
Yes, sir.

259
00:09:15,960 --> 00:09:16,360
Go.

260
00:09:24,360 --> 00:09:25,960
When you first bought this place,

261
00:09:25,960 --> 00:09:26,919
didn't you hire some guys

262
00:09:26,919 --> 00:09:27,759
to clean up?

263
00:09:27,799 --> 00:09:30,559
I checked the wall then, still there,

264
00:09:30,639 --> 00:09:31,240
the same wall.

265
00:09:31,320 --> 00:09:32,279
Not a thing changed.

266
00:09:32,360 --> 00:09:33,480
Couple days later, I came back,

267
00:09:33,600 --> 00:09:35,080
and the wall's gone.

268
00:09:35,200 --> 00:09:36,519
And you became rich.

269
00:09:36,799 --> 00:09:37,840
Inside is the pay

270
00:09:37,879 --> 00:09:38,759
for 133 workers,

271
00:09:38,759 --> 00:09:39,559
you know?

272
00:09:39,759 --> 00:09:40,440
Two million.

273
00:09:40,480 --> 00:09:41,600
Who are you guys?

274
00:09:43,600 --> 00:09:45,879
(2013)
Back off! Back off!

275
00:09:45,919 --> 00:09:48,120
Pay up! Pay up!

276
00:09:48,120 --> 00:09:48,720
Step back!

277
00:09:49,399 --> 00:09:49,799
Enough.

278
00:09:50,120 --> 00:09:50,519
Enough.

279
00:09:51,320 --> 00:09:52,159
Move, move!

280
00:09:52,440 --> 00:09:53,200
Okay, okay!

281
00:09:53,200 --> 00:09:54,919
All right, stop whining!

282
00:09:55,720 --> 00:09:56,519
Get Hu Deshuai out here.

283
00:09:56,559 --> 00:09:57,559
I've told you every day,

284
00:09:57,600 --> 00:09:58,840
but you can't understand.

285
00:09:59,039 --> 00:10:00,480
I've said it a hundred times.

286
00:10:00,559 --> 00:10:01,200
Hu Deshuai

287
00:10:01,480 --> 00:10:02,480
is long gone.

288
00:10:02,559 --> 00:10:03,799
And the cops have been here.

289
00:10:03,840 --> 00:10:05,039
They can't find him either.

290
00:10:05,200 --> 00:10:06,039
How could we possibly

291
00:10:06,039 --> 00:10:06,679
do better than them?

292
00:10:08,039 --> 00:10:08,480
Well...

293
00:10:11,200 --> 00:10:12,399
I found this job for you.

294
00:10:12,679 --> 00:10:13,960
I brought you all up.

295
00:10:14,679 --> 00:10:16,120
I'm seeing this through.

296
00:10:16,320 --> 00:10:17,039
That money,

297
00:10:17,039 --> 00:10:18,000
I will get it back for you.

298
00:10:18,279 --> 00:10:18,679
Later,

299
00:10:18,879 --> 00:10:19,919
everyone writes down their names

300
00:10:20,039 --> 00:10:21,519
and how much they're owed.

301
00:10:21,559 --> 00:10:22,120
Thumbprint it.

302
00:10:24,679 --> 00:10:25,080
San.

303
00:10:26,720 --> 00:10:27,399
Go get an ink pad.

304
00:10:28,960 --> 00:10:29,320
Got it.

305
00:10:37,759 --> 00:10:38,080
Next.

306
00:10:44,159 --> 00:10:45,679
Now the police can't find him either.

307
00:10:46,559 --> 00:10:48,360
Then let's go to labor arbitration.

308
00:10:49,279 --> 00:10:50,440
Get the money back.

309
00:11:04,039 --> 00:11:04,759
Here.

310
00:11:07,120 --> 00:11:08,679
There you go.

311
00:11:08,840 --> 00:11:09,759
Got it. Step back.

312
00:11:10,639 --> 00:11:12,200
My legs are numb.

313
00:11:12,360 --> 00:11:13,000
Here are

314
00:11:13,000 --> 00:11:14,279
all 133 workers.

315
00:11:14,480 --> 00:11:15,600
Names,

316
00:11:15,639 --> 00:11:16,240
amounts owed,

317
00:11:16,360 --> 00:11:17,879
all written down clear as day.

318
00:11:17,919 --> 00:11:18,960
It's been ten years.

319
00:11:19,360 --> 00:11:21,759
Some are gone, pitifully.

320
00:11:22,600 --> 00:11:23,720
Problem, Yitong?

321
00:11:24,200 --> 00:11:25,840
Looks fine to me.

322
00:11:26,000 --> 00:11:28,639
I've asked every agency
that could handle this.

323
00:11:29,200 --> 00:11:31,320
We couldn't find him or the money.

324
00:11:32,559 --> 00:11:32,919
Okay.

325
00:11:33,240 --> 00:11:33,720
I admit,

326
00:11:34,120 --> 00:11:36,559
there was something in the wall.

327
00:11:37,159 --> 00:11:37,919
But nobody can

328
00:11:39,200 --> 00:11:39,639
touch it.

329
00:11:40,159 --> 00:11:40,919
Why?

330
00:11:41,120 --> 00:11:42,039
Because it's not clean.

331
00:11:42,039 --> 00:11:42,919
What do you mean?

332
00:11:42,919 --> 00:11:43,480
The money's dirty.

333
00:11:43,639 --> 00:11:45,639
Dirty money?

334
00:11:45,639 --> 00:11:47,240
Clean money hides in walls?

335
00:11:47,279 --> 00:11:48,320
Touch the wrong thing,

336
00:11:48,320 --> 00:11:48,840
and you're dead.

337
00:11:48,879 --> 00:11:50,879
But the two million is clean.

338
00:11:50,919 --> 00:11:51,399
Yeah.

339
00:11:51,600 --> 00:11:52,399
How do you know

340
00:11:52,440 --> 00:11:53,200
that this two million

341
00:11:53,200 --> 00:11:54,279
came from the wall?

342
00:11:54,720 --> 00:11:55,840
Well...

343
00:11:58,080 --> 00:11:58,559
Well?

344
00:12:00,120 --> 00:12:00,600
I mean...

345
00:12:01,320 --> 00:12:02,600
I don't know.

346
00:12:03,799 --> 00:12:04,200
Fine.

347
00:12:05,240 --> 00:12:05,759
Let's go.

348
00:12:06,559 --> 00:12:07,039
Let's call the cops.

349
00:12:07,600 --> 00:12:08,480
You are the ones

350
00:12:08,480 --> 00:12:09,200
who dug into our place.

351
00:12:09,279 --> 00:12:10,840
Police? Are you sure?

352
00:12:10,919 --> 00:12:11,799
Exactly.

353
00:12:13,840 --> 00:12:14,200
But...

354
00:12:14,639 --> 00:12:15,519
What do you think?

355
00:12:16,600 --> 00:12:17,399
Enough talk.

356
00:12:18,120 --> 00:12:18,639
Listen.

357
00:12:19,399 --> 00:12:20,320
Since we all know

358
00:12:20,320 --> 00:12:21,240
the thing hidden in the wall,

359
00:12:21,360 --> 00:12:21,840
we are

360
00:12:22,120 --> 00:12:22,879
all stuck

361
00:12:22,879 --> 00:12:24,320
on this boat together.

362
00:12:24,519 --> 00:12:25,240
And if it goes down,

363
00:12:25,639 --> 00:12:26,799
none of us are walking away clean.

364
00:12:26,960 --> 00:12:27,279
Exactly.

365
00:12:27,480 --> 00:12:28,720
What's your buddy's name again?

366
00:12:29,080 --> 00:12:29,919
Tomb raider,

367
00:12:30,519 --> 00:12:31,159
San.

368
00:12:32,320 --> 00:12:32,679
San.

369
00:12:32,799 --> 00:12:33,440
So, this San.

370
00:12:33,440 --> 00:12:34,480
He's sick, right?

371
00:12:34,519 --> 00:12:35,799
You should get him to the hospital.

372
00:12:36,039 --> 00:12:36,879
As for that two million,

373
00:12:36,879 --> 00:12:37,919
we'll get it sorted.

374
00:12:38,080 --> 00:12:39,080
If it belongs to you,

375
00:12:39,240 --> 00:12:40,000
we'll make sure

376
00:12:40,279 --> 00:12:41,200
you get every penny.

377
00:12:41,279 --> 00:12:41,600
Right.

378
00:12:42,559 --> 00:12:43,240
Police?

379
00:12:44,399 --> 00:12:45,759
Not necessary.

380
00:12:46,840 --> 00:12:47,879
Don't do it.

381
00:12:48,039 --> 00:12:49,279
We won't call the cops.

382
00:12:50,120 --> 00:12:50,639
But...

383
00:12:50,639 --> 00:12:52,200
When will we know for sure?

384
00:12:52,440 --> 00:12:52,840
No clue.

385
00:12:53,039 --> 00:12:54,320
But we'll risk our lives to find out.

386
00:12:54,480 --> 00:12:54,919
We'll dig.

387
00:12:54,960 --> 00:12:56,240
Or you go check it yourselves.

388
00:12:56,519 --> 00:12:57,679
How's that sound?

389
00:12:58,759 --> 00:12:59,799
How much did San's treatment cost?

390
00:12:59,799 --> 00:13:00,279
How much?

391
00:13:00,399 --> 00:13:01,240
How much did you pay?

392
00:13:03,080 --> 00:13:04,679
About two thousand something.

393
00:13:05,279 --> 00:13:05,840
Let's ask for three.

394
00:13:05,960 --> 00:13:07,919
Three thousand? Really?

395
00:13:07,960 --> 00:13:08,600
What do you think?

396
00:13:12,120 --> 00:13:12,799
Here's ten grand.

397
00:13:13,399 --> 00:13:13,840
Take it.

398
00:13:16,639 --> 00:13:17,399
That much?

399
00:13:17,639 --> 00:13:18,399
I don't know...

400
00:13:18,480 --> 00:13:19,080
Listen,

401
00:13:19,440 --> 00:13:20,799
this is from our own pockets.

402
00:13:20,879 --> 00:13:22,200
Not from the wall stash.

403
00:13:22,720 --> 00:13:23,639
We'll make it right.

404
00:13:24,000 --> 00:13:25,240
So once you earn your share,

405
00:13:25,279 --> 00:13:26,200
make sure it comes back to us.

406
00:13:26,919 --> 00:13:28,200
Yeah, yeah, we will.

407
00:13:28,440 --> 00:13:28,799
One more thing.

408
00:13:28,919 --> 00:13:29,720
After he sees a doctor,

409
00:13:29,960 --> 00:13:31,360
you guys come back and seal this tunnel.

410
00:13:31,360 --> 00:13:31,799
All right?

411
00:13:32,720 --> 00:13:34,279
- Yes. We will.
- Yes. We will.

412
00:13:34,360 --> 00:13:35,519
Thank you, Mr. Yu.

413
00:13:35,639 --> 00:13:36,440
We will get going, then.

414
00:13:36,600 --> 00:13:37,639
Mr. Yu, about that two million...

415
00:13:37,679 --> 00:13:39,120
Move. Stop talking.

416
00:13:40,480 --> 00:13:41,639
Don't forget the sealing.

417
00:13:42,240 --> 00:13:43,039
We'll keep that in mind!

418
00:14:18,799 --> 00:14:19,279
You...

419
00:14:20,600 --> 00:14:21,360
How much does she owe you?

420
00:14:21,639 --> 00:14:22,120
I will pay it.

421
00:14:22,519 --> 00:14:22,960
Money?

422
00:14:23,240 --> 00:14:23,840
What money?

423
00:14:23,960 --> 00:14:25,080
She does not owe us anything.

424
00:14:25,279 --> 00:14:26,440
You said it yourself.

425
00:14:26,559 --> 00:14:27,559
Depreciation fees,

426
00:14:27,679 --> 00:14:28,919
wall damage fees,

427
00:14:29,039 --> 00:14:30,639
bathroom ceiling repair fees,

428
00:14:30,720 --> 00:14:31,679
all kinds of nonsense charges.

429
00:14:31,679 --> 00:14:32,679
That was a misunderstanding.

430
00:14:32,679 --> 00:14:33,120
A misunderstanding.

431
00:14:33,120 --> 00:14:33,960
How could there be

432
00:14:33,960 --> 00:14:35,440
that many ridiculous charges?

433
00:14:36,320 --> 00:14:36,919
Ms. Chen,

434
00:14:37,159 --> 00:14:38,120
if you ever want to move back,

435
00:14:38,240 --> 00:14:39,399
you are welcome anytime.

436
00:14:39,600 --> 00:14:40,159
More than welcome.

437
00:14:40,200 --> 00:14:40,679
No need.

438
00:14:41,159 --> 00:14:41,840
Okay.

439
00:14:42,039 --> 00:14:42,759
Ms. Chen,

440
00:14:42,960 --> 00:14:44,240
I will refund your deposit.

441
00:14:44,519 --> 00:14:45,240
I will transfer it now.

442
00:14:54,039 --> 00:14:54,679
Done.

443
00:14:55,000 --> 00:14:55,720
Where is my luggage?

444
00:14:56,120 --> 00:14:56,639
Go get it.

445
00:14:56,919 --> 00:14:58,039
It is inside.

446
00:15:00,200 --> 00:15:00,600
Here.

447
00:15:01,559 --> 00:15:02,919
You silly thing!

448
00:15:02,919 --> 00:15:04,120
Your hands are all greasy!

449
00:15:07,200 --> 00:15:08,480
Clean. All clean.

450
00:15:08,639 --> 00:15:09,120
Here.

451
00:15:09,879 --> 00:15:10,360
Shiny again.

452
00:15:11,320 --> 00:15:11,799
Of course,

453
00:15:11,960 --> 00:15:13,360
as for the damage and repair costs

454
00:15:13,360 --> 00:15:14,080
for the cello,

455
00:15:14,240 --> 00:15:15,519
we will take responsibility.

456
00:15:16,279 --> 00:15:16,720
But

457
00:15:17,200 --> 00:15:17,720
right now,

458
00:15:17,720 --> 00:15:19,000
we are a little short on cash.

459
00:15:19,159 --> 00:15:20,159
How about this?

460
00:15:20,399 --> 00:15:21,639
Once I collect the rent,

461
00:15:21,679 --> 00:15:22,679
I will transfer it to you.

462
00:15:23,200 --> 00:15:24,480
We are all friends here.

463
00:15:25,000 --> 00:15:25,559
Do me a favor.

464
00:15:26,039 --> 00:15:26,759
Let us stay friends.

465
00:15:27,279 --> 00:15:27,879
All right?

466
00:15:32,080 --> 00:15:32,720
Let me help you.

467
00:15:33,559 --> 00:15:34,000
Thank you.

468
00:15:35,240 --> 00:15:36,679
Come on. Do not be upset.

469
00:15:37,000 --> 00:15:37,960
You got your things back.

470
00:15:38,799 --> 00:15:39,600
People like that landlord

471
00:15:39,600 --> 00:15:40,679
are not worth arguing with.

472
00:15:42,320 --> 00:15:42,879
I'm not upset.

473
00:15:43,960 --> 00:15:44,840
Not worth it.

474
00:15:45,720 --> 00:15:46,919
Then leave your luggage at my place.

475
00:15:47,000 --> 00:15:47,759
I'll take you to fix the cello.

476
00:15:49,799 --> 00:15:50,320
Let's go.

477
00:15:53,730 --> 00:15:55,120
(Songbai Music Shop)

478
00:15:55,120 --> 00:15:56,000
(Songbai Music Shop)
Sixty thousand?

479
00:15:56,519 --> 00:15:57,279
Just to fix it up

480
00:15:57,279 --> 00:15:58,039
costs sixty thousand?

481
00:16:00,320 --> 00:16:01,519
This cello of yours

482
00:16:02,320 --> 00:16:04,120
was imported from Europe.

483
00:16:05,600 --> 00:16:06,720
Fully handmade.

484
00:16:07,960 --> 00:16:09,159
It is no longer in production.

485
00:16:10,200 --> 00:16:10,639
Look.

486
00:16:13,200 --> 00:16:14,559
The bow is horsehair.

487
00:16:15,480 --> 00:16:16,759
The strings are gut.

488
00:16:17,440 --> 00:16:18,840
This is no ordinary piece.

489
00:16:20,720 --> 00:16:22,360
No. That is too expensive.

490
00:16:22,639 --> 00:16:23,159
Buying another one

491
00:16:23,159 --> 00:16:24,159
would not cost sixty thousand.

492
00:16:25,240 --> 00:16:25,919
All right.

493
00:16:27,080 --> 00:16:27,799
I can give you a discount.

494
00:16:29,320 --> 00:16:30,000
Fifty-four thousand.

495
00:16:31,559 --> 00:16:32,519
Or you can skip the repair

496
00:16:33,200 --> 00:16:34,120
and look around

497
00:16:34,879 --> 00:16:35,840
for a new one.

498
00:16:42,120 --> 00:16:42,679
Forget it.

499
00:16:44,720 --> 00:16:46,039
It can be fixed. Why not?

500
00:16:47,480 --> 00:16:48,279
I will take you somewhere.

501
00:16:57,810 --> 00:16:59,610
(Luzhou Song and Dance Troupe)

502
00:17:21,839 --> 00:17:22,440
Mr. Yu?

503
00:17:24,559 --> 00:17:25,119
Mr. Yu?

504
00:17:28,000 --> 00:17:28,960
Come in, quickly.

505
00:17:29,079 --> 00:17:29,720
Before he gets here.

506
00:17:29,920 --> 00:17:30,640
Hurry.

507
00:17:32,640 --> 00:17:33,599
Or he will throw me out.

508
00:17:47,680 --> 00:17:48,400
Yunluo.

509
00:17:49,759 --> 00:17:50,440
Have you ever seen it?

510
00:17:51,839 --> 00:17:52,400
I know it.

511
00:17:53,720 --> 00:17:54,799
It is rare, though.

512
00:17:56,400 --> 00:17:57,480
Of course it is.

513
00:17:58,480 --> 00:18:00,240
Yu Ming's great-grandfather,

514
00:18:00,759 --> 00:18:01,880
Yu Zhenqiu,

515
00:18:02,000 --> 00:18:03,480
was a court musician.

516
00:18:03,559 --> 00:18:04,200
More or less,

517
00:18:04,359 --> 00:18:05,440
when he was about seven,

518
00:18:05,440 --> 00:18:06,319
he started working with

519
00:18:06,680 --> 00:18:07,279
Gongche notation.

520
00:18:07,440 --> 00:18:08,119
This instrument is used

521
00:18:08,119 --> 00:18:08,799
in Shifan ancient music.

522
00:18:13,599 --> 00:18:14,240
Do not mess with it.

523
00:18:15,680 --> 00:18:17,240
Yu Ming's grandpa was impressive too.

524
00:18:17,680 --> 00:18:18,799
Huqin, Western instruments,

525
00:18:18,799 --> 00:18:19,599
he could handle them all.

526
00:18:19,960 --> 00:18:21,079
And Yu Ming's father,

527
00:18:22,240 --> 00:18:23,319
if your instrument has any problem,

528
00:18:23,319 --> 00:18:23,880
give it to him.

529
00:18:23,880 --> 00:18:24,920
He will fix it.

530
00:18:25,279 --> 00:18:25,960
Yu Ming

531
00:18:25,960 --> 00:18:26,960
may be a mess now,

532
00:18:27,200 --> 00:18:28,319
but his family

533
00:18:28,559 --> 00:18:29,200
had real talent.

534
00:18:38,039 --> 00:18:38,519
Mr. Yu.

535
00:18:40,559 --> 00:18:41,039
You are back.

536
00:18:41,799 --> 00:18:42,279
Have you eaten?

537
00:18:42,920 --> 00:18:43,359
Not yet.

538
00:18:44,720 --> 00:18:45,200
Hello, Mr. Yu.

539
00:18:45,559 --> 00:18:46,000
Hi.

540
00:18:46,519 --> 00:18:47,680
I need a favor.

541
00:18:48,480 --> 00:18:49,000
What is it?

542
00:18:49,759 --> 00:18:50,440
This cello...

543
00:18:51,079 --> 00:18:51,599
Do show it to me.

544
00:18:52,559 --> 00:18:53,200
I have no time.

545
00:18:55,319 --> 00:18:56,599
I damaged someone's cello.

546
00:18:56,599 --> 00:18:57,519
Please help me out.

547
00:18:58,000 --> 00:19:00,519
I am at work, not taking jobs.

548
00:19:01,200 --> 00:19:02,440
Help me out this once.

549
00:19:02,440 --> 00:19:03,000
Come on.

550
00:19:03,640 --> 00:19:04,720
I tried people outside,

551
00:19:04,720 --> 00:19:06,279
but their work is not good enough.

552
00:19:06,880 --> 00:19:07,920
Just take a look first.

553
00:19:08,039 --> 00:19:09,000
It is a fine cello.

554
00:19:09,000 --> 00:19:09,880
You will like it.

555
00:19:30,319 --> 00:19:31,680
This is a fine cello.

556
00:20:01,540 --> 00:20:03,720
(2016)

557
00:20:03,720 --> 00:20:04,880
(2016)
Since you came to Germany,

558
00:20:06,079 --> 00:20:07,279
you have never gone back, have you?

559
00:20:13,359 --> 00:20:14,480
You told that man

560
00:20:15,319 --> 00:20:16,160
you would go back,

561
00:20:17,119 --> 00:20:17,599
didn't you?

562
00:20:19,039 --> 00:20:19,680
I don't know

563
00:20:19,680 --> 00:20:20,720
whether I ever will.

564
00:20:23,200 --> 00:20:23,920
Back then,

565
00:20:25,319 --> 00:20:26,279
I wanted it alone,

566
00:20:27,759 --> 00:20:28,799
and I made myself suffer,

567
00:20:30,119 --> 00:20:30,920
him too.

568
00:20:32,839 --> 00:20:33,480
Pei Wen'an?

569
00:20:40,440 --> 00:20:41,720
You are the Shiyi she mentioned.

570
00:20:47,799 --> 00:20:48,519
She was my senior.

571
00:20:54,880 --> 00:20:55,680
Leave the cello here.

572
00:20:56,279 --> 00:20:58,359
When it's fixed, I'll call Shiqi.

573
00:20:59,119 --> 00:20:59,799
You may go.

574
00:21:03,000 --> 00:21:03,680
Thank you, Mr. Yu.

575
00:21:24,680 --> 00:21:26,400
So, your senior and Mr. Yu,

576
00:21:26,680 --> 00:21:27,400
what exactly were they?

577
00:21:33,240 --> 00:21:33,839
I want a drink.

578
00:21:36,400 --> 00:21:36,960
Okay.

579
00:21:54,680 --> 00:21:56,599
(1993)
Lately, I have been studying

580
00:21:56,920 --> 00:21:59,599
(1993)
Schoenberg's twelve-tone system,

581
00:22:00,440 --> 00:22:01,920
and it only deepens my feeling

582
00:22:02,440 --> 00:22:04,720
that the symphony
will never come to an end.

583
00:22:05,839 --> 00:22:07,559
The way each part answers another,

584
00:22:07,920 --> 00:22:09,839
the feeling in a symphonic poem,

585
00:22:10,359 --> 00:22:12,359
there is endless beauty in it.

586
00:22:12,400 --> 00:22:12,920
That is interesting.

587
00:22:12,960 --> 00:22:13,400
I don't get it.

588
00:22:13,440 --> 00:22:13,880
Who is it for?

589
00:22:13,920 --> 00:22:16,599
I wonder if you would be willing

590
00:22:16,640 --> 00:22:17,680
this Saturday afternoon,

591
00:22:18,200 --> 00:22:19,519
after the salon performance,

592
00:22:20,000 --> 00:22:21,200
to discuss Bruckner's

593
00:22:21,200 --> 00:22:22,039
musical structure with me.

594
00:22:23,880 --> 00:22:25,160
The architectural aesthetics

595
00:22:25,200 --> 00:22:26,519
you once spoke of

596
00:22:27,160 --> 00:22:28,240
are fully present here.

597
00:22:29,400 --> 00:22:30,799
I would also like to discuss

598
00:22:31,119 --> 00:22:32,839
the cycles of cosmic space.

599
00:22:33,799 --> 00:22:36,279
I eagerly await your reply.

600
00:22:43,640 --> 00:22:44,440
Shameless.

601
00:22:45,200 --> 00:22:46,640
And she calls herself educated.

602
00:22:46,759 --> 00:22:48,000
He already has a wife.

603
00:22:48,160 --> 00:22:49,480
Look what she is doing.

604
00:23:28,720 --> 00:23:30,079
I cannot live like this anymore.

605
00:23:30,240 --> 00:23:31,880
Do I even matter to you?

606
00:23:32,000 --> 00:23:32,920
Why would she write you

607
00:23:32,920 --> 00:23:33,680
a letter like that?

608
00:23:37,440 --> 00:23:38,319
What are you looking at?

609
00:23:39,240 --> 00:23:40,039
What is there to see?

610
00:23:40,440 --> 00:23:41,680
Have you nothing better to do?

611
00:23:42,119 --> 00:23:43,599
Crowding someone's door for gossip?

612
00:23:43,839 --> 00:23:44,960
Go home. Now.

613
00:23:45,440 --> 00:23:46,599
Stop blocking our door.

614
00:23:47,079 --> 00:23:48,640
Go on. Leave.

615
00:23:49,240 --> 00:23:50,599
I have nothing to hide.

616
00:23:51,079 --> 00:23:52,160
My conscience is clear.

617
00:23:55,359 --> 00:23:56,240
But how

618
00:23:57,000 --> 00:23:58,279
did things ever come

619
00:23:58,279 --> 00:23:59,240
to this?

620
00:24:02,599 --> 00:24:04,839
Stop pushing each other.

621
00:24:08,799 --> 00:24:10,079
Everyone is laughing at us.

622
00:24:10,160 --> 00:24:11,480
Don't come back anymore.

623
00:24:12,240 --> 00:24:13,119
This is all your fault.

624
00:24:13,240 --> 00:24:14,680
I never want to see you again.

625
00:24:20,519 --> 00:24:21,720
Where do you think you are going?

626
00:24:22,440 --> 00:24:24,119
Now you care about dignity?

627
00:24:24,599 --> 00:24:26,680
Pei Wen'an ran off in shame.

628
00:24:27,079 --> 00:24:29,400
You're still playing the devoted man.

629
00:24:31,079 --> 00:24:31,920
If you have nothing to hide,

630
00:24:31,960 --> 00:24:32,880
